    • Constructor Detail

      • UmlClass

        public UmlClass​(java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String content)
        The constructors must defines the name (tag) of the class and its string content. All other attributes are defined as empty first and should be accessed with the createXXX or addXXX methods to put new element in them.
        Parameters:
        name - the actual name of the class.
        content - the String content representation of the class. The content should define everything the class has and be coherent with how the UcdParser expect it to be formatted.

      • updateScreen

        public void updateScreen​(ScreenController controller)
        Description copied from interface: Displayable
        Required to transfer the action to the ScreenController. The screen controller should implement a method to itself handle the event. Typical usage could be : 

         public void updateScreen(ScreenController controller) {
     controller.updateSelection(this);
 }
        where updateSelection() does the heavy update work.
        Specified by:
        updateScreen in interface Displayable
        Parameters:
        controller - the screen controller used to dispatch event.

      • accept

        public void accept​(UmlVisitor visitor)
        Description copied from interface: UmlVisitorElement
        This method is used to redirect the operations to be completed upon visiting to the corresponding method in UmlVisitor. Basic implementation should look like : 
             public void accept(UmlVisitor visitor) {
         visitor.visit(this);
     }
        As such, the appropriate method in the UmlVisitor will be called
        Specified by:
        accept in interface UmlVisitorElement
        Parameters:
        visitor - the visitor on which the operation to be performered is defined.

      • csvFormat

        public java.lang.String csvFormat​(boolean selfUcd)
        Description copied from interface: CsvFormatter
        This method defines how the class should be converted into a csv row. If multiple class implement this interface and wants to be written to a same .csv file, they must make sure that
        1. They provide the same number of column
        2. The columns have the same semantics
        3. they provide a line return for each row
        4. They should not insert more than onw row
        5. The class must use CsvFormatter.SEPERATOR to seperate columns on the same row
        If those condition are satisfied, FileController.createCsvFile(String, Collection) can be used without fearing any problems.
        Specified by:
        csvFormat in interface CsvFormatter
        Parameters:
        selfUcd - tells FileController.createCsvFile(String, Collection) if it should try to create the csvfile for the current project or a ganeral file. Should usually be set to false to create a general csv file.
        Returns:
        The string representation of the row to be added to the csv file.
